---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <address>
      Marc Borer<br />
      Hirzengarten 2<br />
      4226 Breitenbach<br />
      Schweiz
    </address>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:mb@marc-borer.ch">mb@marc-borer.ch</a></p>

    <h2>2. General</h2>
    <p>
      Protecting your personal data is important to us. This privacy policy informs you
      about the collection and processing of personal data when using this website in
      accordance with the Swiss Data Protection Act (nDSG) and, where applicable, the
      European General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>3. Hosting and Server Logs</h2>
    <p>
      This website is hosted on <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>, a service provided by
      GitHub, Inc., 88 Colin P Kelly Jr St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA.
    </p>
    <p>
      When you access this website, the following data is automatically collected in
      server logs and processed by GitHub:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address</li>
      <li>Date and time of the request</li>
      <li>Requested page (URL)</li>
      <li>Referrer URL</li>
      <li>Browser type and version (User-Agent)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data is processed by GitHub to ensure the operation and security of the service.
      For more information, see the
      <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Google Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This website uses <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> (Property ID: G-YDWCY6XBPN),
      a web analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street,
      Dublin 4, Ireland.
    </p>
    <p>
      Google Analytics is <strong>only activated after your explicit consent</strong> via
      our cookie banner. Without your consent, no analytics data is collected.
    </p>
    <p>The following data is processed upon consent:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Page views and session duration</li>
      <li>Approximate location (based on anonymized IP address)</li>
      <li>Device and browser information</li>
      <li>Referrer (where you came from)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Google Analytics 4 anonymizes IP addresses by default. It is not possible for us
      to identify you personally.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Opt-out:</strong> You can withdraw your consent at any time by selecting
      "Decline" in the cookie banner or by deleting the <code>cookie-consent</code>
      entry in your browser's LocalStorage. Alternatively, you can use the
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
    <p>This website uses:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>LocalStorage</strong> (not a cookie): <code>cookie-consent</code> — stores your cookie banner decision (accepted/declined)</li>
      <li><strong>LocalStorage</strong> (not a cookie): <code>theme</code> — stores your preferred color scheme (light/dark)</li>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics cookies</strong> — only set after your consent (e.g., <code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code>)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Data Transfer to the USA</h2>
    <p>
      By using GitHub Pages and Google Analytics, data is transferred to the USA. The USA
      currently has an adequacy decision under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (DPF) and
      the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework. Both providers are certified under the DPF.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under the Swiss Data Protection Act (nDSG) and, where applicable, the GDPR, you
      have the following rights:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — You may request information about your stored personal data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — You may request the correction of inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> — You may request the deletion of your data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> — You may request the restriction of data processing</li>
      <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> — You may receive your data in a common format</li>
      <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — You may object to the processing of your data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise your rights, please contact:
      <a href="mailto:mb@marc-borer.ch">mb@marc-borer.ch</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      If you believe that the processing of your data violates data protection law, you
      may file a complaint with the Swiss Federal Data Protection and Information Commissioner
      (FDPIC): <a href="https://www.edoeb.admin.ch" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.edoeb.admin.ch</a>
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      This privacy policy may be updated at any time. The current version is available
      on this page.
    </p>
    <p class="legal-date">Last updated: April 2026</p>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: var(--space-16) 0;
    max-width: 50rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal p,
  .legal address {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .legal ul {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal code {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .legal-date {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
